The paper deals with signal processing and optimization techniques for sparse signals, which are common topics in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of restricted isometry property (RIP) and restricted orthogonality constant (ROC) also suggests a possible connection to Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the focus on a specific algorithm (Simultaneous Orthogonal Matching Pursuit) may indicate a potential fit with the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
